cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the blocklength-limited throughput of a two-hop relaying network under the assumption of outdated channel state information (CSI). This is a core topic in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies the performance of a relaying network, which is a key topic in networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of a system (relaying network) under the assumption of outdated CSI, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.COM (Computational Complexity) - The paper does not directly deal with computational complexity, but it involves mathematical analysis and modeling, which can be related to computational complexity.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not deal with multimedia directly, but it involves the analysis of communication systems, which can be related to multimedia communication.
